<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1933,2024]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1436,151,349]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1999,2024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,435,2000,2024]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[449,551,2000,2024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00153). Carapace length 
<number box="[1011,1046,2000,2024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.6">1.6</number>
(variation 
<number box="[1168,1254,2000,2024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.5" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.6</number>
, n= 
<number box="[1298,1313,2000,2024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
); abdomen length 
<number box="[228,266,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.9">1.9</number>
. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[402,488,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 71 – 74" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1077,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,1077,1923]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 71 – 74. Ilargus moronatigus sp. nov. 71 female holotype, dorsal view; 72 female left chelicera, back view; 73 epigynum, ventral view; 74 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 71, 0.5 mm; 72, 0.2 mm; 73 – 74, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209896/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[455,488,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="72.0">72</number>
</figureCitation>
): yellow brown. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[959,997,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, II 
<number box="[1035,1073,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.1">2.1</number>
, III 
<number box="[1121,1159,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.6">2.6</number>
, IV 
<number box="[1208,1246,151,175]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="3.4">3.4</number>
. Epigynum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 71 – 74" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1077,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,1077,1923]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 71 – 74. Ilargus moronatigus sp. nov. 71 female holotype, dorsal view; 72 female left chelicera, back view; 73 epigynum, ventral view; 74 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 71, 0.5 mm; 72, 0.2 mm; 73 – 74, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209896/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,186,210]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="73.0">73</number>
</figureCitation>
): window small; opening at posterior margin of window. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[945,1034,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURES 71 – 74" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1077,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,1077,1923]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 71 – 74. Ilargus moronatigus sp. nov. 71 female holotype, dorsal view; 72 female left chelicera, back view; 73 epigynum, ventral view; 74 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 71, 0.5 mm; 72, 0.2 mm; 73 – 74, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209896/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[1001,1034,186,210]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="74.0">74</number>
</figureCitation>
): copulatory duct thin and slightly convoluted, with accessory gland near the beginning; spermatheca almost kidney-shaped. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 71 – 74" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1077,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,1077,1923]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 71 – 74. Ilargus moronatigus sp. nov. 71 female holotype, dorsal view; 72 female left chelicera, back view; 73 epigynum, ventral view; 74 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 71, 0.5 mm; 72, 0.2 mm; 73 – 74, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209896/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,255,279]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="71.0">71</number>
</figureCitation>
): carapace gray brown with indistinct yellowish markings, eye area dark brown, thoracic area with a narrow yellowish brown stripe; abdomen dark brown, with light yellow speckles and markings; legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
